Text.SourceString: I want to play with the kitties.
Text.LocalizedString: I want to play with the kitties.

Text.SourceString: It's kind of weird seeing you here, 'cause you're, like, super old.
Text.LocalizedString: It's kind of weird seeing you here, 'cause you're, like, super old.

Text.SourceString: Ugh, studying is such a drag.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, studying is such a drag.

Text.SourceString: I wanna go outside.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, can I go to your farm after school?
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna go outside.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, can I go to your farm after school?

Text.SourceString: I wish we could have school outside every day. It's way more fun than being cooped up indoors!
Text.LocalizedString: I wish we could have school outside every day. It's way more fun than being cooped up indoors!

Text.SourceString: Hmm, I'm getting hungry. Tacos sound yummy right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, I'm getting hungry. Tacos sound yummy right now.

Text.SourceString: I'm gonna go bug hunting later with Oliver. Wanna join?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm gonna go bug hunting later with Oliver. Wanna join?

Text.SourceString: Do you have cows on your farm? Can I come over and pet them?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have cows on your farm? Can I come over and pet them?

Text.SourceString: I wish our house was big enough to have cows. But Mom said we'd have to move the TV area if we wanted them.//<portrait=normal>I think I like my TV better.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish our house was big enough to have cows. But Mom said we'd have to move the TV area if we wanted them.//<portrait=normal>I think I like my TV better.

Text.SourceString: Mom is super strict. She said I can do whatever I want, but I can't bring home the bugs I find. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom is super strict. She said I can do whatever I want, but I can't bring home the bugs I find. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: It's our school day today, but at least we get to be outside.
Text.LocalizedString: It's our school day today, but at least we get to be outside.

Text.SourceString: I asked Mr. Barnes why we have to start school so early. Like, wouldn't we learn better if we were more rested?//<portrait=normal>I vote we move school to 11 am.
Text.LocalizedString: I asked Mr. Barnes why we have to start school so early. Like, wouldn't we learn better if we were more rested?//<portrait=normal>I vote we move school to 11 am.

Text.LocalizedString: I wanna grab some basil pasta, but I'm not sure if I've got enough cash.//Meh, I'll ask Mom later.

Text.SourceString: Today's weather is so beautiful!
Text.LocalizedString: Today's weather is so beautiful!

Text.SourceString: I hiked up with Mom and Dad to the Deep Forest yesterday. The view from the top was amazing! It was tiring, but totally worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: I hiked up with Mom and Dad to the Deep Forest yesterday. The view from the top was amazing! It was tiring, but totally worth it.

Text.SourceString: I'm gonna challenge Oliver to a race later—I'm totally gonna win again.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm gonna challenge Oliver to a race later—I'm totally gonna win again.

Text.SourceString: I saw a bunch of capybaras near the stream while I was exploring the forest.//<portrait=normal>It was so cool to see them up close.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a bunch of capybaras near the stream while I was exploring the forest.//<portrait=normal>It was so cool to see them up close.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever gone cliff diving near the lighthouse?//I wanna try it someday, but it seems kinda scary!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever gone cliff diving near the lighthouse?//I wanna try it someday, but it seems kinda scary!

Text.SourceString: Valentina told me that sometimes some of her mom's friends gather around at the beach and make a fire pit.//<portrait=surprised>It sounds so fun, I need to get my friends to do it.
Text.LocalizedString: Valentina told me that sometimes some of her mom's friends gather around at the beach and make a fire pit.//<portrait=surprised>It sounds so fun, I need to get my friends to do it.

Text.SourceString: You know that cavern near the river? The one in the forest?//<portrait=surprised>Millie said it's not safe...monsters and massive bugs supposedly live there. Is that true?
Text.LocalizedString: You know that cavern near the river? The one in the forest?//<portrait=surprised>Millie said it's not safe...monsters and massive bugs supposedly live there. Is that true?

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the puppies at the shelter? They're so cute!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the puppies at the shelter? They're so cute!

Text.SourceString: I made friends with a stray pigeon near my house. Named it Captain Whiskers.
Text.LocalizedString: I made friends with a stray pigeon near my house. Named it Captain Whiskers.

Text.SourceString: Studying for history tests is boring. I'd rather be doing something fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Studying for history tests is boring. I'd rather be doing something fun.

Text.SourceString: I found the coolest seashell collection over there. Wanna check it out?
Text.LocalizedString: I found the coolest seashell collection over there. Wanna check it out?

Text.SourceString: I'm planning to spend my summer exploring every hidden corner of Coral Island. Who's in?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm planning to spend my summer exploring every hidden corner of Coral Island. Who's in?

Text.SourceString: I've got a whole list of goals: learn to surf, master the art of beach volleyball, and maybe even conquer my fear of cliff diving.//<portrait=happy>Oh, and eating ice cream for dinner! Ha ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: I've got a whole list of goals: learn to surf, master the art of beach volleyball, and maybe even conquer my fear of cliff diving.//<portrait=happy>Oh, and eating ice cream for dinner! Ha ha ha.

Text.LocalizedString: Our house gets stuffy at night. Mom needs to buy an AC.

Text.SourceString: I tried counting the palm trees around the beach the other day and lost track.//Now I gotta start over.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried counting the palm trees around the beach the other day and lost track.//Now I gotta start over.

Text.SourceString: I wish Mom would chill out a bit.//Being a teenager with a 7 o'clock curfew is so unfair.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish Mom would chill out a bit.//Being a teenager with a 7 o'clock curfew is so unfair.

Text.SourceString: Can't wait for <Italic>uni</>, where I can set my own schedule.//Need to focus on my wildlife study, some of those critters only come out at night.
Text.LocalizedString: Can't wait for <Italic>uni</>, where I can set my own schedule.//Need to focus on my wildlife study, some of those critters only come out at night.

Text.SourceString: Gah, volleyball was rough last week. Sprained my ankle, but it's all good now, thankfully.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah, volleyball was rough last week. Sprained my ankle, but it's all good now, thankfully.

Text.SourceString: Gotta grab some new socks. These ones just aren't cutting it.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta grab some new socks. These ones just aren't cutting it.

Text.SourceString: Mom's cooking is the bomb, especially her burritos.//Awh, I'm gonna miss them when I'm away in <Italic>uni</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom's cooking is the bomb, especially her burritos.//Awh, I'm gonna miss them when I'm away in <Italic>uni</>.

Text.SourceString: When I bring a boy over, Mom insists the room's gotta be opened up. Ugh, so embarrassing.//Can't a girl have some privacy? It's not like we're doing anything funny...it's just Archie.//We're playing with rocks, for crying out loud.
Text.LocalizedString: When I bring a boy over, Mom insists the room's gotta be opened up. Ugh, so embarrassing.//Can't a girl have some privacy? It's not like we're doing anything funny...it's just Archie.//We're playing with rocks, for crying out loud.

Text.SourceString: Oh, uh, my toe is itchy.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, uh, my toe is itchy.

Text.SourceString: I'm gonna see if I can find some flowers to bring home later.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm gonna see if I can find some flowers to bring home later.

Text.SourceString: Archie's thinking of becoming a vet. Sounds kinda cool, right?//I might check it out.
Text.LocalizedString: Archie's thinking of becoming a vet. Sounds kinda cool, right?//I might check it out.

Text.SourceString: Today's freezing. I just wanna crawl back into bed and stay there forever.
Text.LocalizedString: Today's freezing. I just wanna crawl back into bed and stay there forever.

Text.SourceString: Snow days are awesome until you're soaked through. So, yeah, there's that.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow days are awesome until you're soaked through. So, yeah, there's that.

Text.LocalizedString: Not allowed to swim at the beach anymore 'cause the water's getting too cold.//But hey, at least the hot spring's still open.

Text.SourceString: You gotta dry your boots before coming to our house or my mom's gonna be so angry at you.
Text.LocalizedString: You gotta dry your boots before coming to our house or my mom's gonna be so angry at you.

Text.SourceString: Wow, this storm is intense! I hope the power doesn’t go out.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow, this storm is intense! I hope the power doesn’t go out.

Text.SourceString: I love watching the lightning.//<portrait=surprised>Oh! Maybe I'll just sit by the window and watch the storm for a bit!
Text.LocalizedString: I love watching the lightning.//<portrait=surprised>Oh! Maybe I'll just sit by the window and watch the storm for a bit!

Text.SourceString: Awesome, it's raining! I can’t wait to go play in the puddles later.
Text.LocalizedString: Awesome, it's raining! I can’t wait to go play in the puddles later.

Text.SourceString: My plants are going to be so happy about this rain.
Text.LocalizedString: My plants are going to be so happy about this rain.

Text.SourceString: I hope this storm doesn’t wreck my garden. Fingers crossed!
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this storm doesn’t wreck my garden. Fingers crossed!

Text.LocalizedString: I should’ve put some fertilizer in the garden yesterday. The rain would have helped it soak in perfectly.

Text.SourceString: I should’ve put some fertilizer in the garden yesterday. The rain would have helped it soak in perfectly.
Text.LocalizedString: I should’ve put some fertilizer in the garden yesterday. The rain would have helped it soak in perfectly.

Text.LocalizedString: I’m not going anywhere in this weather. Yeah...

Text.LocalizedString: I'm super excited! We're getting ready for the Ogoh-Ogoh show for the Spooky Festival. It's going to be epic.

Text.LocalizedString: Hey, are you joining the beach cleanup this week? My parents signed me up, so I guess I’ll be there.//It'll actually be fun, I think.

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow’s going to be awesome—no school and we’re grilling at Alun Alun. I can’t wait!
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow’s going to be awesome—no school and we’re grilling at Alun Alun. I can’t wait!

Text.SourceString: You should've seen how many fish I caught at the lake yesterday! It was incredible.
Text.LocalizedString: You should've seen how many fish I caught at the lake yesterday! It was incredible.

Text.SourceString: We're bringing Bonbon to the animal festival later this week. He's really excited about it!
Text.LocalizedString: We're bringing Bonbon to the animal festival later this week. He's really excited about it!

Text.SourceString: Bonbon had a blast at the festival yesterday! We took tons of photos—wanna see?
Text.LocalizedString: Bonbon had a blast at the festival yesterday! We took tons of photos—wanna see?

Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if you need to actually have a big farm to join the harvest festival.//I mean, mom and I have a garden and it's like, produces stuff...so...

Text.LocalizedString: We just harvested the most delicious pumpkin—it was so fresh! I think it'll make amazing ice cream.

Text.LocalizedString: I just planted some sunflowers. Hopefully, they shoot up fast!

Text.LocalizedString: Mom and I just planted strawberries in our garden. Can’t wait to see them full-grown!

Text.LocalizedString: We totally forgot to pick our crops yesterday, and now they’re all ruined.

Text.LocalizedString: Oops, I totally forgot that sunflowers don't do well in Spring. The seeds we planted ended up drying out.

Text.LocalizedString: We totally forgot to pick our crops yesterday, and now they’re all ruined.

Text.LocalizedString: Uncle Mark got me into gardening when I was little. I'm really glad he did because it's turned out to be super fun!

Text.LocalizedString: I thought about being an explorer like Uncle Mark, but now it seems a bit too risky and the food on those trips? Not so great.

Text.LocalizedString: If only Bonbon could talk, we could sing and make music together. That would be amazing!

Text.LocalizedString: I’m not sure why Uncle Mark is so into shiitake mushrooms. They're alright, but nothing special, I guess.

Text.LocalizedString: There's a winter fair soon, right at the beach and at night... I'm still deciding if I should go.

Text.SourceString: Boat rides are awesome! I'm so looking forward to riding the frog boat again next year.
Text.LocalizedString: Boat rides are awesome! I'm so looking forward to riding the frog boat again next year.

Text.LocalizedString: Have you noticed the festival poster near the community center keeps changing?//I’ve never seen anyone changing it. Could it be Valentina's uncle?

Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I hear strange noises at night. I think they’re just wild animals, which is kind of cool!

Text.SourceString: My friends are all talking about getting starter jobs, maybe at Sam’s or the inn... I haven't really thought about it much.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe I could shadow Chaem at the beach? But then again, I'm not the best swimmer, so...
Text.LocalizedString: My friends are all talking about getting starter jobs, maybe at Sam’s or the inn... I haven't really thought about it much.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe I could shadow Chaem at the beach? But then again, I'm not the best swimmer, so...

Text.LocalizedString: There are loads of crabs at our beach, and Dad says that's totally normal.//I actually like watching them do their little crab dances!

Text.LocalizedString: I need to check if our feeder has enough hay.//<portrait=concerned>Dad reminded me last week, but I totally forgot.

Text.LocalizedString: I'm really hoping Mom makes tacos tonight. Yum!

Text.LocalizedString: Dippa is the coolest! They taught me how to paint chickens.//<portrait=normal>I’ve got the painting in my room. Dippa said it might be worth a lot someday, and I believe them.

Text.LocalizedString: My uncle is obsessed with calendars, which is kind of odd. So I get him a new calendar every birthday.//He's always so thrilled about it. Valentina’s right, grown-ups are weird!

Text.LocalizedString: Hey there! What’s up?

Text.SourceString: Hi! How’s it going?
Text.LocalizedString: Hi! How’s it going?

Text.SourceString: Hey, um...yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, um...yeah?

Text.SourceString: You have a cool name, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I wish my name was <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>Ah, but nah, it doesn't fit me. I think 'Zoe' suits me best.
Text.LocalizedString: You have a cool name, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I wish my name was <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>Ah, but nah, it doesn't fit me. I think 'Zoe' suits me best.

Text.LocalizedString: I did really bad on my last chem test, and Mom wasn't too happy about it.//Ugh, I need to study a bit harder.

Text.LocalizedString: I'm glad I'm an only child. I love having the whole bedroom to myself...well, except for Bonbon. He's basically my brother!

Text.LocalizedString: Valentina's mom made her own hand cream. Don't tell her, but it smells kind of funny.//<portrait=normal>It did work well, though, because it healed my cracked hands right up!

Text.LocalizedString: Next week, I'm planning to check on my pet rocks. They're out by the house.//I wonder how they're doing.

Text.LocalizedString: My knees have been hurting. Dad thinks it's just a growth spurt and says it's normal.

Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I’m super hungry! It seems like I’m always hungry these days.

Text.LocalizedString: I tried growing my hair out like my mom's, but it takes like, a million years to dry, so yeah...nope!

Text.LocalizedString: I’m so excited for the Cherry Blossom Festival this week! The trees are gonna look amazing.

Text.LocalizedString: I hope I find lots of worms at Alun-Alun tomorrow. Fingers crossed!

Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday was awesome! I found so many worms under the trees.

Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna go to Alun-Alun again this weekend with Dad.//We’re gonna see who can find the most worms!

Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to ride on the frog boat! I’m gonna note down all the fish I spot.

Text.LocalizedString: Last year, I spotted 27 fish on my way to the Tree Planting Festival.//<portrait=normal>It was awesome!

Text.LocalizedString: Mom brought some hummus to the picnic yesterday. Bleh!

Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow is Summer! Yay!

Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to pet all the animals at the festival! I’m gonna pet them all.

Text.LocalizedString: I asked Millie if I could help decorate the town for the Animal Festival, but she said I had to ask my mom first.

Text.LocalizedString: Did you see Bonbon dancing yesterday? It was hilarious!

Text.LocalizedString: They should totally let fish join the Animal Festival. It’s unfair they get left out of the fun.

Text.LocalizedString: Starlet Town’s festivals are so cool! There’s environmental stuff, parties, and music.//<portrait=normal>I’m definitely gonna miss them when I go to <Italic>uni</>.

Text.LocalizedString: I picked up so much trash at the Beach Cleanup yesterday. The beach is so clean now!

Text.LocalizedString: I'm ready for Fall!

Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been busy making safe food for the wildlife. I’m bringing it to the Harvest Festival so people can feed the ducks with it.//It's much healthier for them than human scraps.

Text.LocalizedString: I wanted to bring my crops for the display contest on the 15th, but they’re not ready yet.//Fingers crossed they’ll be ready in time!

Text.LocalizedString: Oh no, my crop isn’t ready for the contest tomorrow. Oh well, at least I’ve got plenty of wildlife food to share.

Text.SourceString: Did I tell you about the time Uncle Mark rescued a hawk with a broken wing? He’s like a superhero!
Text.LocalizedString: Did I tell you about the time Uncle Mark rescued a hawk with a broken wing? He’s like a superhero!

Text.SourceString: Mom's taught me so much about taking care of animals. I helped her nurse a puppy back to health last week!
Text.LocalizedString: Mom's taught me so much about taking care of animals. I helped her nurse a puppy back to health last week!

Text.SourceString: Every time I see Bonbon’s gray fur, it reminds me he’s getting older.//<portrait=normal>I’m trying to make every day special for him.
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I see Bonbon’s gray fur, it reminds me he’s getting older.//<portrait=normal>I’m trying to make every day special for him.

Text.SourceString: Group projects can be a pain, but at least I’m working with Archie this time. He’s super smart.
Text.LocalizedString: Group projects can be a pain, but at least I’m working with Archie this time. He’s super smart.

Text.SourceString: I got an A on my history test! All that studying really paid off.
Text.LocalizedString: I got an A on my history test! All that studying really paid off.

Text.SourceString: I gotta study for my <Italic>bio</> exam tomorrow. Ugh...
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta study for my <Italic>bio</> exam tomorrow. Ugh...

Text.SourceString: We’re starting a new book in English class, and it’s actually really interesting.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re starting a new book in English class, and it’s actually really interesting.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the latest episode of Masked Detective? It was so intense!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the latest episode of Masked Detective? It was so intense!

Text.SourceString: I went to the beach with my family last weekend. We saw so many cool birds!
Text.LocalizedString: I went to the beach with my family last weekend. We saw so many cool birds!

Text.SourceString: I found this really interesting plant next to my house. I need to look it up in my nature book.
Text.LocalizedString: I found this really interesting plant next to my house. I need to look it up in my nature book.

Text.SourceString: I caught a frog by the pond today! Don’t worry, I let it go after.
Text.LocalizedString: I caught a frog by the pond today! Don’t worry, I let it go after.

Text.SourceString: We have this fun family tradition of making egg custard every Sunday morning.//<portrait=happy>It’s my uncle’s favorite!
Text.LocalizedString: We have this fun family tradition of making egg custard every Sunday morning.//<portrait=happy>It’s my uncle’s favorite!

Text.SourceString: Bonbon came home soaking wet yesterday.//I guess he wanted to swim like Taco. Ha ha! Now the whole house smells like a wet towel.//<portrait=normal>Mom’s pretty upset.
Text.LocalizedString: Bonbon came home soaking wet yesterday.//I guess he wanted to swim like Taco. Ha ha! Now the whole house smells like a wet towel.//<portrait=normal>Mom’s pretty upset.

Text.SourceString: We’re having a family movie night tonight. I can’t wait to watch something fun.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re having a family movie night tonight. I can’t wait to watch something fun.

Text.SourceString: My dog did the cutest thing today! He chased his tail for like, five minutes.
Text.LocalizedString: My dog did the cutest thing today! He chased his tail for like, five minutes.

Text.SourceString: I learned a lot about dolphins in school today. They’re so smart!
Text.LocalizedString: I learned a lot about dolphins in school today. They’re so smart!

Text.SourceString: Bonbon brought in a mouse again. I think he's trying to impress us.
Text.LocalizedString: Bonbon brought in a mouse again. I think he's trying to impress us.

Text.SourceString: I’m making a scrapbook of all my nature photos. It’s turning out great!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m making a scrapbook of all my nature photos. It’s turning out great!

Text.SourceString: Weekend means volleyball! I could stay at the beach all day.
Text.LocalizedString: Weekend means volleyball! I could stay at the beach all day.
